name: Bowen Reef Diving Tour
description: Set out on an unforgettable journey to Bowen’s famous Horseshoe Bay Reef with our guided diving tour. Departing from the Airlie Beach Dive Centre, this experience offers a mesmerizing dive into vibrant coral gardens. Ideal for certified divers of all levels, the shallow yet thriving underwater world at Bowen Reef, with a maximum depth of just 7 meters, provides an accessible and stunning environment for exploration. Encounter a rainbow of healthy corals, juvenile fish, turtles, and more in clear waters, perfect for underwater photography and observing delicate reef ecosystems.
includes:
All dive equipment
Return trip from Airlie Beach to Bowen Reef
Professional dive guide
highlights:
Explore Bowen’s famous Horseshoe Bay Reef
Dive into vibrant coral gardens
Encounter a variety of marine life including turtles and moray eels
Ideal for underwater photography
Shallow depths with great visibility

name: Fun Night Dive Tour
description: Dive into the enchanting nights of the Whitsundays Reefs on an unforgettable night dive adventure. Perfect for certified divers seeking a unique and intimate underwater experience, this tour offers a thrilling opportunity to witness the vibrant nightlife of Bowen Reef's Coral Garden. Explore the reef's healthy, colorful corals and encounter a variety of nocturnal marine life, including turtles, moray eels, and bioluminescent plankton. This safe and supportive environment ensures a memorable experience for divers of all levels.
includes:
All dive equipment
Dive guide
Return trip from Airlie Beach to Bowen Reef
highlights:
Experience the vibrant nightlife of Bowen Reef's Coral Garden
Witness nocturnal marine life in action
Encounter turtles, moray eels, and bioluminescent plankton
Safe and thrilling dive environment
Suitable for certified divers of all levels

name: SS Yongala Wreck Dive
description: Embark on a once-in-a-lifetime diving adventure at the legendary SS Yongala, a world-renowned wreck dive site celebrated as one of Australia’s most captivating underwater attractions. This experience offers a perfect blend of rich history, diverse marine life, and awe-inspiring exploration. Dive into history as you explore the SS Yongala, a passenger ship that tragically sank in 1911 and has since transformed into a vibrant underwater haven. Home to a spectacular array of marine life, this wreck is teeming with giant groupers, curious sea turtles, eagle rays, colorful coral formations, and even sharks. Whether you’re captivated by marine life or the mysteries of history, this dive offers a truly unique experience you’ll cherish forever.
includes:
Two Guided Wreck Dives
All essential gear
Wreck Dive and Deep Dive E-learning
Round-Trip Transport from Airlie Beach
highlights:
Explore the majestic SS Yongala
Guided by highly-trained dive instructors
Dive into history with a shipwreck from 1911
Witness a vibrant underwater ecosystem
Encounter giant groupers, sea turtles, eagle rays, and sharks
price_tiers: PADI Advanced Open Water Certification: A$250
